:::summary
Repentance is the process of turning from sin toward God — a complete change of mind, heart, and conduct made possible by the Atonement of Jesus Christ. It is the second principle of the gospel and the essential response to sin for any person who wishes to receive God's forgiveness and return to His presence. Latter-day Saint theology teaches that repentance is not merely a one-time event but an ongoing, lifelong orientation of the soul toward Christ.
:::

